I don't concur that charm is in and of itself overpowered (the NPCs might be), the bigger problem is wizards draw far too much aggro doing their one and only job.<br>
<br>
I play both a wizard and an enchanter.  When I have a charmed pet, I can do a lot of damage, but the neat side effect is, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I do it with almost no aggro to myself</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Even when charm breaks, the aggro generated is about 1 point.  A couple swings from a warrior can get an ex-charmed pet's attention.<br>
<br>
When I'm playing my wizard, however, I just cannot chain cast SoS.  Even if I had the mana regen to chain cast with impunity, three or four casts on an XP mob would get me unceremoniously hauled to it's feet for a stompin'.<br>
<br>
That's where the major current weakness in the wizard class lies, I believe.  We have these big booms but can't use them because of the inefficiency.<br>
<br>
Sticking to draughts I have a much better time of it.  <br>
<br>
If only rain spells actually..you know...worked properly and paid attention to real resists.<br>
<br>
