(1) How many level 65 mages are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>really</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> soloing in BoT each day?  The 1 zone in the whole game which this charm spell is useful btw.  And a mage with pet breaking charm = dead probably.  No root, snare, mez, blah blah blah.<br>
(2) Although Burnout 5 does stick with enchanter haste, that haste part of the components do NOT actually stack.<br>
<br>
Speed of Vallon<br>
Increase AGI by 52 <br>
Increase DEX by 33 <br>
Increase ATK by 41 <br>
Increase Attack Speed by 68%<br>
<br>
Burnout 5 <br>
Increase AC by 22 <br>
Increase STR by 80 <br>
Increase Attack Speed by 85% <br>
Increase ATK by 40 <br>
<br>
You can put both of these spells on the mage pet, but it won't be 153% hasted, just some of the other items will all stack together.<br>
<br>
(3)  And as they mentioned above, these spells are all under testing for changes which would make it impossible to haste the charmed pet.<br>
